an attempt to gain my two books.  I will eventually get them.  I'm not worried.   At the same time, I like to see people that deserve items win.  If someone wins a COF on a roll and beats me out, that's fine.  If someone wins a roll on an item only to run to EC to sell it... That I have a problem with.<br><br>What I don't like to see are people greedily sniping items as soon as they hit the floor.  They ruin my night, as well as other people's (Sometimes in upwards of 50 people)<br><br><br>Some names come to mind.<br><br>- Dollaine with his COF fiasco &quot;It's mine, and I'm taking it...&quot;<br>- That Druid that looted the NO DROP Polished Mithril Torque off of Tranix right after I had called out that it was there and stood up from the corpse.  She was in my group as well, so I got to WATCH her do it....  Wish I remembered her name... I'll know it if I see it.<br>- Bouffy the Druid that ninja'd the Spoon off of Cazel in Oasis (There was ONE ANGRY chanter that night)<br><br>Those are the only ones I can think of, but I'm sure that there are many more.<br><br>Point is guys, the raid went fine.  Everyone got their chance to roll, and everyone was happy.  In the end, does it really matter?  This was one of the better raids I've been on.  At least the RBB turned up. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Something to think about.<br> <p><HR><center><a href="http://luclin.dhs.org/triad/icbio.cfm?ICName=Marque"><img src="http://luclin.dhs.org/triad/images/ic/marque_sig.jpg" border="0"></a><h3>Call me a midget again, and I'll cook your prostate.</h3><HR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ullaynoroth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Llaynoroth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Scowling Poster</span><br> <font color=#778899>(3/13/02 4: